THREE men have been arrested following a disturbance at a Glasgow flat.
Police were called to the scene in Shaw Street, Govan, at about 4.15am.
Armed police were deployed during the incident.
Govan Road was closed for a time between Golspie Street and Burleigh Street while police dealt with the incident but later reopened.
A Police Scotland spokesman said: &quot;At about 4.15am this morning police were called to a disturbance at a flat in Shaw Street.&quot;
Three men have been arrested in connection with the incident.&quot;
